{"Title": "Semantic-based Automated Reasoning for AWS Access Policies using SMT", "Year": 2019, "Source": "Proc. Conf. Formal Methods Comput.-Aided Des., FMCAD", "Volume": null, "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 206, "PageEnd": 214, "CitedBy": 12, "DOI": "10.23919/FMCAD.2018.8602994", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85061662139&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2018 FMCAD Inc.Cloud computing provides on-demand access to IT resources via the Internet. Permissions for these resources are defined by expressive access control policies. This paper presents a formalization of the Amazon Web Services (AWS) policy language and a corresponding analysis tool, called ZELKOVA, for verifying policy properties. ZELKOVA encodes the semantics of policies into SMT, compares behaviors, and verifies properties. It provides users a sound mechanism to detect misconfigurations of their policies. ZELKOVA solves a PSPACE-complete problem and is invoked many millions of times daily.", "AuthorKeywords": null, "IndexKeywords": ["Access control policies", "Access policies", "Amazon web services", "Analysis tools", "Automated reasoning", "Misconfigurations", "Policy language", "PSPACE-complete problems"], "DocumentType": "Conference Proceeding", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-85061662139", "SubjectAreas": [["Computer Graphics and Computer-Aided Design", "COMP", "1704"], ["Software", "COMP", "1712"]], "AuthorData": {"55871996100": {"Name": "Backes J.", "AuthorID": "55871996100", "AffiliationID": "60076757", "AffiliationName": "Amazon Web Services"}, "57188571711": {"Name": "Bolignano P.", "AuthorID": "57188571711", "AffiliationID": "60076757", "AffiliationName": "Amazon Web Services"}, "13008902100": {"Name": "Cook B.", "AuthorID": "13008902100", "AffiliationID": "60076757", "AffiliationName": "Amazon Web Services"}, "57206261153": {"Name": "Dodge C.", "AuthorID": "57206261153", "AffiliationID": "60076757", "Affiliat